        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. A, C, Neoliomera pubescens (H. Milne Edwards, 1873), lectotype male (30.5 × 17.5 mm) (MNHN), Mauritius; D, Neoliomera demani Forest & Guinot, 1961, paratype male (23.0 × 13.0 mm) (MNHN), Tahiti; B, E, Neoliomera fragraea n. sp., holotype male (18.3 × 10.1 mm) (ZRC 2014.0206), Guam. A, B, left G1; C–E, distal parts of left G1s. A, C, after Forest & Guinot (1961: fig. 75); D, after Forest & Guinot (1961: fig. 76)." ;
