        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 6. A–D, Neoliomera pubescens (H. Milne Edwards, 1834), dried lectotype male (30.5 × 17.5 mm) (MNHN-B10037), Mauritius; E, F, Neoliomera demani Forest & Guinot, 1961, paratype male (23.0 × 13.0 mm) (MNHN-B10035), Tahiti; G, Neoliomera demani Forest & Guinot, 1961, holotype male (38.0 × 21.0 mm) (MNHN), Hikueru, French Polynesia. A, dorsal view; B, frontal view of carapace; C, E, dorsal views of carapaces; D, F, G, outer views of left chelae. A, B, after A. Milne- Edwards (1865: pl. 12 fig. 6); C, D, after Forest & Guinot (1961: pl. 3 figs. 1, 2); E–G, after Forest & Guinot (1961: pl. 3 figs. 3–5)." ;
